	<p>
		Hi, I'm Shana — a Washington DC-based Airbnb Superhost, Guest Favorite, and the person
		behind Hosting Decoded.
	</p>

	<p>
		I didn't start hosting with a playbook. I learned by doing — setting up my first property,
		figuring out pricing the hard way, and sending one too many 11pm texts to guests who
		couldn't find the thermostat. Over time, I built systems that made hosting feel less like
		a second job and more like a business I actually enjoyed running.
	</p>

	<p>
		One of the first systems I built was a proper guest guidebook. Not a Google Doc with
		bullet points — a real, professional welcome guide that answered every question before
		guests thought to ask it. The difference in reviews was immediate. Guests started
		mentioning it by name. The "communication" and "check-in" scores on my reviews
		improved. And my phone got a lot quieter during stays.
	</p>

	<p>
		I looked for a template that matched the level of care I put into my properties and
		couldn't find one. Everything out there was either generic, poorly designed, or made by
		someone who had clearly never hosted a guest. So I built my own.
	</p>

	<p>
		That template — <a href="https://shanadesigns.gumroad.com/l/airbnb-guidebook-template">The Complete Airbnb Guidebook</a> — is now available
		for any host who wants to skip the trial and error. It's designer-crafted, fully editable
		in Canva, and takes under an hour to customize for your property. Built on what actually
		works — not what looks good in a mockup.
	</p>

	<h2>What Hosting Decoded Is</h2>

	<p>
		Hosting Decoded is the resource hub I wish had existed when I started. Every article,
		tip, and tool here comes from real experience running short-term rentals in one of the
		most competitive markets in the country.
	</p>

	<p>I write about three things:</p>

	<ul>
		<li><strong>Guest Experience</strong> — how to create stays that earn 5-star reviews and repeat guests</li>
		<li><strong>Hosting 101</strong> — the fundamentals new hosts need to get right from day one</li>
		<li><strong>Earnings</strong> — pricing strategy, revenue optimization, and scaling smart</li>
	</ul>

	<p>
		If you're just getting started or trying to level up a property you already have,
		you're in the right place.
	</p>

